01:10:30,777 --> 01:10:33,746
Did you know there were once ads

921
01:10:33,813 --> 01:10:37,442
that said four out of five doctors
recommend this brand or that brand?

922
01:10:37,517 --> 01:10:39,610
Come on. You're kidding me.

923
01:10:39,686 --> 01:10:43,747
- Doctors used to recommend cigarettes?
- Said they were good for you.

924
01:10:43,823 --> 01:10:46,951
There was one slogan before my time:

925
01:10:47,026 --> 01:10:49,425
"Not a cough in the carload. "

926
01:10:51,129 --> 01:10:54,292
It's a little too late now.

927
01:10:54,366 --> 01:10:56,891
I'm sorry.

928
01:11:08,747 --> 01:11:10,840
You like our Tom Dobbs, do you?

929
01:11:13,285 --> 01:11:15,275
Unfortunately, I do.

930
01:11:15,353 --> 01:11:17,514
I see that.

931
01:12:00,830 --> 01:12:03,298
- I have to talk to you in private.
- Now?

932
01:12:03,366 --> 01:12:05,527
- Yes.
- OK.

933
01:12:22,384 --> 01:12:24,375
Thanks.

934
01:12:29,792 --> 01:12:32,124
You've got a great group.

935
01:12:32,194 --> 01:12:34,593
Ellie, whatever your problem is...

936
01:12:34,662 --> 01:12:37,426
What? You can fix my problem?

937
01:12:37,498 --> 01:12:42,800
Is this the president-elect speaking
or just Tom Dobbs the comedian?

938
01:12:42,870 --> 01:12:45,304
- Just Tom Dobbs.
- Good.

939
01:12:45,373 --> 01:12:51,710
Because Tom Dobbs is not the elected President
of the United States. There. I've said it. Kill me.

940
01:12:59,353 --> 01:13:02,048
It's true.

941
01:13:02,122 --> 01:13:06,024
There was a problem
with the computer voting system.

942
01:13:06,093 --> 01:13:10,792
I tried to warn them. It's that error that's made you
the next President of the United States.

943
01:13:10,864 --> 01:13:13,560
- I didn't win?
- Not even close.

944
01:13:13,633 --> 01:13:16,033
- What do you want me to do?
- I don't know.

945
01:13:16,103 --> 01:13:19,368
I had to say it. I've been living with this.
I just had to tell you.

946
01:13:19,439 --> 01:13:21,873
- Do you want to go public with this?
- I can't.

947
01:13:21,942 --> 01:13:24,775
I could, but nobody would believe me.
Not anymore.

948
01:13:24,845 --> 01:13:28,439
But somebody has to know.
Somebody. At least you.

949
01:13:28,514 --> 01:13:30,778
I mean, I don't know.
Look, I don't know.

950
01:13:30,850 --> 01:13:37,187
Maybe it is best that you're the next President
of the United States even if they didn't vote for you.

951
01:13:38,858 --> 01:13:41,622
Out of curiosity...

952
01:13:41,694 --> 01:13:44,254
- did you vote for me?
- No.

953
01:13:44,330 --> 01:13:47,060
I don't vote.
To be honest with you, I don't vote.

954
01:13:47,133 --> 01:13:50,967
Politicians will say anything in the world
to get elected. Maybe I'm jaded.

955
01:13:51,036 --> 01:13:54,164
Honestly, I didn't even think you had a chance.

956
01:13:54,240 --> 01:13:58,835
I know it's ironic I'm talking like I'm concerned.
I don't even vote.

957
01:13:58,910 --> 01:14:02,846
I'm gonna talk this over with Menken.
Come on, I want you with me. Come with me.

958
01:14:02,914 --> 01:14:04,541
- No, I can't.
- Why not?

959
01:14:04,616 --> 01:14:06,777
- Tom, I can't!
- Why?

960
01:14:07,786 --> 01:14:11,483
I had to tell you.
You do with it what you want.

961
01:14:17,095 --> 01:14:19,256
Happy Thanksgiving.

962
01:14:23,834 --> 01:14:25,995
Happy Thanksgiving.

963
01:14:42,252 --> 01:14:44,584
<i>Is something wrong?</i>

964
01:14:47,191 --> 01:14:49,522
You guys have a fight?

965
01:14:50,860 --> 01:14:55,126
She knows a lot about computers.
More than you ever wanna know, really.

966
01:14:55,198 --> 01:14:57,530
Should I be impressed?

967
01:14:59,402 --> 01:15:01,666
It's improbable, me winning the election.

968
01:15:01,737 --> 01:15:06,231
Well, Mark Twain once wrote, "The only
difference between reality and fiction

969
01:15:06,309 --> 01:15:09,472
"is that fiction needs to be credible. "

970
01:15:09,545 --> 01:15:12,378
We are, my friend, in uncharted waters.

971
01:15:12,882 --> 01:15:14,850
She just told me
I didn't win the election.

972
01:15:14,917 --> 01:15:16,315
Whoops.

973
01:15:16,384 --> 01:15:19,353
Computer malfunction.

974
01:15:19,421 --> 01:15:22,413
- She knows this? For sure?
- Yeah.

975
01:15:23,758 --> 01:15:27,524
She tried to warn the Delacroy Company
and they hid it. Bad for business.

976
01:15:27,596 --> 01:15:31,623
- You don't believe her, do you?
- I do. It's true.

977
01:15:32,367 --> 01:15:35,632
I always thought the TV Nielsen ratings
were full of shit, but this?

978
01:15:35,704 --> 01:15:38,036
<i>It's hard to believe
that many people watched JAG.</i>

979
01:15:38,106 --> 01:15:41,667
<i>I never met anybody who'd say,
"Hey, did you see JAG last night?"</i>

980
01:15:41,743 --> 01:15:44,734
Don't believe her so quickly, Tom.

981
01:15:44,812 --> 01:15:48,680
- She knows what she's talking about.
- That's debatable.

982
01:15:48,749 --> 01:15:52,583
So... what's she gonna do?

983
01:15:52,653 --> 01:15:55,053
Nothing. She left it up to me.

984
01:15:55,122 --> 01:16:02,255
Leaving it to you. Well, Delacroy's not gonna say
anything, and she's not gonna say anything, so...

985
01:16:02,329 --> 01:16:03,353
there's no problem.

986
01:16:03,430 --> 01:16:05,955
- No problem?
- We move on.

987
01:16:06,033 --> 01:16:09,524
- Oh, like nothing happened?
- Something like that.

988
01:16:09,602 --> 01:16:15,563
If you tell a joke and it stinks
but you put a laugh track over it, the joke still stinks.

989
01:16:15,642 --> 01:16:17,940
I'm President, but not really.

990
01:16:18,011 --> 01:16:23,506
This is where we are.
You wanna throw it away or go for it?

991
01:16:23,583 --> 01:16:26,313
I never told you which gigs to take,
I only advised,

992
01:16:26,386 --> 01:16:32,120
but to me this decision is a slam dunk.

993
01:16:33,192 --> 01:16:35,285
Yeah.

994
01:16:49,541 --> 01:16:50,439
<i>Tom?</i>

995
01:16:50,509 --> 01:16:54,878
Eleanor, tomorrow at 11 o'clock
I'm gonna have a press conference

996
01:16:54,947 --> 01:16:59,384
and tell the American people that
I'm not the legitimate President of the United States.

997
01:17:00,752 --> 01:17:02,776
I'm so sorry.

998
01:17:02,853 --> 01:17:05,481
I- I'll call you tomorrow, OK?

999
01:17:21,872 --> 01:17:24,238
Danny, I told him.

1000
01:17:24,308 --> 01:17:26,776
<i>Why did you tell him?</i>

1001
01:17:26,844 --> 01:17:29,903
I had to. And now I hate myself.

1002
01:17:29,980 --> 01:17:31,277
<i>Does he believe you?</i>

1003
01:17:31,348 --> 01:17:35,842
<i>He's calling a press conference at 11
tomorrow. He's gonna make the whole thing known.</i>

1004
01:17:35,919 --> 01:17:38,285
<i>Oh, shit. Look what you did.</i>

1005
01:17:38,355 --> 01:17:40,585
<i>I wish I hadn't told him.</i>

1006
01:17:40,657 --> 01:17:44,889
<i>I mean, I know I did the right thing.
I know I did the right thing. It was the right thing to do.</i>

1007
01:17:44,961 --> 01:17:47,327
<i>And yet... And yet...</i>

1008
01:17:47,397 --> 01:17:53,029
<i>m- m-maybe I've done the wrong thing,
and how can that possibly be?</i>

1009
01:17:53,103 --> 01:17:55,832
<i>I mean, did I do the right thing
or did I do the wrong thing?</i>

1010
01:17:55,904 --> 01:17:58,498
<i>I know it's the right thing to do,
so why do I feel like this?</i>

1011
01:18:04,747 --> 01:18:08,740
We've got to preempt his press conference.

1012
01:18:11,887 --> 01:18:14,879
And very early tomorrow morning.

1013
01:18:48,122 --> 01:18:52,080
- Press conference set up?
- Uh, yeah. What the hell's going on?

1014
01:18:54,428 --> 01:18:56,328
OK.

