01:18:57,397 --> 01:18:59,524
Jack? Jack?

1016
01:18:59,599 --> 01:19:02,762
Got a reporter says Delacroy's
going to make a major announcement.

1017
01:19:02,836 --> 01:19:05,771
Some big story,
something to do with Eleanor Green.

1018
01:19:05,839 --> 01:19:07,773
<i>This is what we got going on today.</i>

1019
01:19:07,841 --> 01:19:11,208
<i>They're called the Witches of November.
A storm from the Great Lakes.</i>

1020
01:19:11,278 --> 01:19:14,941
<i>That's going to spread one to three inches of snow
right across the D.C. area.</i>

1021
01:19:15,015 --> 01:19:18,142
<i>I don't think there's any more than that,
not a lot of moisture here.</i>

1022
01:19:18,217 --> 01:19:21,414
<i>It's a pretty closed-up system,
and it's gonna move up quickly...</i>

1023
01:19:23,189 --> 01:19:27,683
<i>We interrupt this broadcast
to bring you this breaking news.</i>

1024
01:19:27,760 --> 01:19:31,423
<i>We have some dirty laundry
that needs to be addressed.</i>

1025
01:19:31,497 --> 01:19:37,595
<i>Recently Delacroy had to dismiss
an employee, Eleanor Green,</i>

1026
01:19:37,670 --> 01:19:42,630
<i>who was suffering severe psychological problems.
We made an effort to get her medical help,</i>

1027
01:19:42,708 --> 01:19:48,543
<i>and subsequently discovered that she was heavily
involved in the use of barbiturates and cocaine.</i>

1028
01:19:48,613 --> 01:19:53,073
<i>We would have kept this private, but additional facts
concerning Miss Green have come to light.</i>

1029
01:19:53,151 --> 01:19:58,054
<i>We have evidence that Miss Green manipulated
the prototype of our computer voting system.</i>

1030
01:20:00,725 --> 01:20:02,955
- Tom here.
- Turn on the television.

1031
01:20:03,027 --> 01:20:05,188
- What channel?
- Any channel.

1032
01:20:08,967 --> 01:20:11,935
<i>Her motives aren't quite clear to us,</i>

1033
01:20:12,002 --> 01:20:15,995
<i>apart from the fact that
she seemed obsessed with Tom Dobbs,</i>

1034
01:20:16,073 --> 01:20:20,669
<i>to the degree that she actually tried to corrupt
the computer system to get him elected.</i>

1035
01:20:23,347 --> 01:20:27,443
<i>We also know that the president-elect
has been seen in her presence recently,</i>

1036
01:20:27,518 --> 01:20:33,354
<i>but let me make this clear - we are not suggesting
any impropriety on behalf of the president-elect.</i>

1037
01:20:33,423 --> 01:20:37,051
<i>- Pull over.
- We are a family at Delacroy.</i>

1038
01:20:37,126 --> 01:20:39,594
<i>We have an extensive healthcare program.</i>

1039
01:20:39,662 --> 01:20:45,032
Lots of people have psychological problems, mental
problems, health problems of one kind or another.

1040
01:20:45,101 --> 01:20:48,332
It's not something you sweep under the rug,
you gotta talk about it.

1041
01:20:48,404 --> 01:20:54,604
<i>We believe that strongly, and we make our best effort
to find out about it as soon as possible and give help.</i>

1042
01:20:54,677 --> 01:21:00,775
<i>The good news is, all the computer voting systems
installed in polling stations remained secure.</i>

1043
01:21:00,850 --> 01:21:07,186
Therefore, there were no irregularities in the election
and our safeguards proved to be impenetrable.

1044
01:21:07,255 --> 01:21:12,887
<i>And that's all the information that we have at this time.
I'll take any questions now, if you got 'em. Yes?</i>

1045
01:21:12,961 --> 01:21:17,489
Take a look at this. Take a look at this.
Perfect, just perfect.

1046
01:21:17,566 --> 01:21:22,401
She's a piece of work, huh? Flipped out
in the company cafeteria, on all sorts of drugs.

1047
01:21:22,470 --> 01:21:27,669
Clearly a mental case. Hospital said
she had more pills in her than a pharmacy.

1048
01:21:27,742 --> 01:21:29,936
I believe her.

1049
01:21:30,844 --> 01:21:32,175
She didn't seem that crazy.

1050
01:21:32,246 --> 01:21:38,947
You're in love with her. She could tell you Gandhi ate
hot dogs and you'd believe her. Take a look at this.

1051
01:21:39,019 --> 01:21:42,182
If what she says is true,
I'm really not the president-elect.

1052
01:21:42,256 --> 01:21:44,952
"If" is becoming a very large word.

1053
01:21:45,025 --> 01:21:48,825
Did you forget the first time we met her,
she said she was working for the FBI?

1054
01:21:48,896 --> 01:21:52,730
She said she knew about the computer fraud,
but takes three weeks to tell you.

1055
01:21:52,800 --> 01:21:55,633
"By the way, you're not the President.
Happy Thanksgiving. "

1056
01:21:55,703 --> 01:22:00,071
If she's not psychotic she's a stalker,
and if she's not a stalker she's a CIA operative.

1057
01:22:00,139 --> 01:22:03,040
- Or maybe, just maybe, she's a succubus.
- What's that?

1058
01:22:03,109 --> 01:22:07,705
A succubus is some sort of a demon
that sucks the life out of healthy men.

1059
01:22:07,780 --> 01:22:09,509
I was once a healthy man.

1060
01:22:09,582 --> 01:22:13,211
What are you talking about? Please, please stop.

1061
01:22:13,286 --> 01:22:15,083
Don't get off track.

1062
01:22:41,446 --> 01:22:45,542
Can I get change for this, please?
My dollar won't work in your machine.

1063
01:22:45,617 --> 01:22:48,643
You're that Miss Green from the television.

1064
01:22:48,720 --> 01:22:52,052
I wasn't sure, 'cause you always pay cash.

1065
01:22:52,957 --> 01:22:55,391
- Did your uncle get ahold of you?
- What?

1066
01:22:55,459 --> 01:22:59,793
Your uncle. He was trying to call your room.
He said he couldn't get through.

1067
01:22:59,864 --> 01:23:02,298
By the way, that machine doesn't work.

1068
01:23:36,766 --> 01:23:38,529
<i>Yes, sir.</i>

1069
01:23:38,601 --> 01:23:41,399
Yes, sir. I'm in her hotel now.

1070
01:23:43,640 --> 01:23:46,267
I think she may have figured out the glitch.

1071
01:23:57,686 --> 01:24:01,019
Bring it back, bring her back.
I want constant updates.

1072
01:24:01,090 --> 01:24:04,457
<i>Yes, sir. When I find her,
I know what to do.</i>

1073
01:24:05,894 --> 01:24:10,728
Boy, if she's figured out this computer glitch and goes
with that to the press, we're royally screwed.

1074
01:24:10,798 --> 01:24:12,459
Mm-hm.

1075
01:24:12,633 --> 01:24:13,793
Mm-hm.

1076
01:24:13,868 --> 01:24:19,966
Mr. President, we have that luncheon speech
followed by a White House meet-and-greet.

1077
01:24:20,041 --> 01:24:21,372
What do I do?

1078
01:24:21,442 --> 01:24:24,309
Go be presidential.

1079
01:24:39,059 --> 01:24:44,429
<i>...speech today will give
some insight into the Eleanor Green situation.</i>

1080
01:24:45,399 --> 01:24:47,993
Jack, I've been trying to call her
but I can't reach her.

1081
01:24:48,068 --> 01:24:51,060
<i>You have a busy schedule.
Keep your head in that. Period.</i>

1082
01:24:51,138 --> 01:24:52,605
That's terrific.

1083
01:24:52,672 --> 01:24:54,902
<i>Saturday Night Live wants you.
What do you think?</i>

1084
01:24:54,975 --> 01:24:57,239
<i>- Did I hear "Saturday Night Live"?
- Yeah.</i>

1085
01:24:57,310 --> 01:24:58,743
<i>- Do it.
- Why?</i>

1086
01:24:58,812 --> 01:25:03,875
Because it's a great opportunity. Say you were
blinded by love, you didn't know she was popping pills.

1087
01:25:03,950 --> 01:25:08,283
It isn't like you were in some side street
gettin' head like, uh, Hugh, uh, whatshisname.

1088
01:25:08,354 --> 01:25:12,154
You're so sensitive.
OK. I'll do it.

1089
01:25:12,224 --> 01:25:15,955
Yep, he'll do it.
I'll call you later for details.

1090
01:25:16,028 --> 01:25:19,088
It's hard to believe it's a year
since we've gathered together,

1091
01:25:19,165 --> 01:25:22,965
but we are very pleased
to have a most honored guest with us...

1092
01:25:23,035 --> 01:25:28,598
I wrote down some lines for you. They're fantastic,
if I must say so. I even threw in an old Hitler joke.

1093
01:25:28,674 --> 01:25:31,403
- How's that supposed to work?
- You'll see.

1094
01:25:31,476 --> 01:25:34,104
...Tom Dobbs!

1095
01:25:34,179 --> 01:25:36,170
Knock 'em dead.

1096
01:25:45,390 --> 01:25:47,824
Thank you very much.

1097
01:25:47,892 --> 01:25:50,759
I guess we should
get this over with at the beginning,

1098
01:25:50,829 --> 01:25:56,324
because you've all heard there's
a little bit of a rumor going around right now.

1099
01:25:56,401 --> 01:26:00,336
So I'll share the big scoop with you,
'cause, uh, Oprah was booked.

1100
01:26:02,072 --> 01:26:07,442
I'm not even President of the United States yet,
and I'm involved in a scandal with a woman.

1101
01:26:09,980 --> 01:26:13,211
<i>I did not have sex with that woman.</i>

1102
01:26:13,283 --> 01:26:15,274
I wanted to.

1103
01:26:15,352 --> 01:26:17,877
I'm single.

1104
01:26:17,955 --> 01:26:25,258
And, uh, you've elected a man as President who is
probably the unluckiest man in the world in that area.

1105
01:26:25,328 --> 01:26:30,630
In high school,
most of my dates were with myself.

1106
01:26:30,700 --> 01:26:33,294
I would take myself out for dinner,
bring myself home,

1107
01:26:33,369 --> 01:26:36,202
put on music that I liked,

1108
01:26:36,272 --> 01:26:42,643
have my way with myself and then go,
"Should I drive myself home now?"

1109
01:26:44,113 --> 01:26:47,173
Pretty much the bottom line.
If I was in Italy I might get lucky.

1110
01:26:47,250 --> 01:26:50,947
They elected an Italian porn star to their senate.

1111
01:26:51,020 --> 01:26:56,719
Which is wonderful. There's no sex scandal there,
just great posters and incredible downloads.

1112
01:26:58,627 --> 01:27:01,528
<i>I think that's the bottom line. In a democracy,</i>

1113
01:27:01,596 --> 01:27:04,394
<i>we can have a sense of humor
about ourselves. We have to.</i>

1114
01:27:04,466 --> 01:27:07,765
You're allowed to make fun of those in power.

1115
01:27:07,836 --> 01:27:12,068
But even in the face of tyranny there is comedy.
Two old Jews were sent to kill Hitler.

1116
01:27:12,140 --> 01:27:17,305
They waited in an alleyway. They were supposed to
kill Hitler at 12:30. They have guns, bombs, knives.

1117
01:27:17,379 --> 01:27:19,539
12:30, no Hitler.

1118
01:27:19,613 --> 01:27:21,740
12:45, no Hitler.

1119
01:27:21,815 --> 01:27:24,409
One o'clock, no Hitler.

1120
01:27:24,485 --> 01:27:28,512
Finally one turns to the other and goes,
"My God, I hope nothing happened to him. "

1121
01:27:30,991 --> 01:27:36,019
<i>It's good to see us back. The fact that we can laugh is
wonderful. But the last few years we've been divided.</i>

1122
01:27:36,096 --> 01:27:38,656
Red states, blue states.

1123
01:27:38,732 --> 01:27:44,034
There are no red and blue states, there's only the
United States of America. That's what we're about.

1124
01:27:44,104 --> 01:27:50,064
That's why I say you can't spend 200 million dollars
on a campaign and not be owing people something.

1125
01:27:50,143 --> 01:27:53,169
Next thing you know
they have to deal with the special interests,

1126
01:27:53,246 --> 01:27:57,376
they're doing special favors for special people
and not dealing with what you need:

1127
01:27:57,450 --> 01:28:00,385
Education, healthcare, environmental issues.

1128
01:28:00,453 --> 01:28:07,222
They have to deal with oil companies, chemical
companies, drug companies, and they owe them.

1129
01:28:07,293 --> 01:28:10,490
And in the process, people get neglected.

1130
01:28:10,563 --> 01:28:15,499
The poor have no advocate,
because the poor can't afford a lobbyist.

1131
01:28:15,567 --> 01:28:18,468
The Statue of Liberty says,
"Give me your tired, your poor,"

1132
01:28:18,537 --> 01:28:21,131
not "your wealthy, your gifted and your endowed. "

1133
01:28:24,810 --> 01:28:27,836
<i>I worked out your bit with SNL.
They really liked it.</i>

1134
01:28:27,913 --> 01:28:30,279
- Has Eleanor called the headquarters yet?
- No.

1135
01:28:30,349 --> 01:28:33,807
- She hasn't called me either.
- Well, you never know with females.

1136
01:28:33,885 --> 01:28:37,548
I had an ex who used to do enough tranquillizers
to put a flock of sheep to sleep.

1137
01:28:37,623 --> 01:28:38,816
Why?

1138
01:28:38,889 --> 01:28:42,950
- She said it made the sex with me more bearable.
- Eleanor didn't do drugs.

1139
01:28:43,027 --> 01:28:47,623
Oh, no. And ball players don't do steroids,
they just wake up one day looking like Mack trucks.

1140
01:28:47,698 --> 01:28:50,997
- Pump a little iron, you look like a Humvee.
- With little tiny balls.

1141
01:28:51,068 --> 01:28:53,696
<i>This is a meet-and-greet, nothing more.</i>

1142
01:28:53,771 --> 01:28:57,104
<i>Oh, the house is so close to the street.</i>

1143
01:28:58,309 --> 01:29:01,676
Whoa, boy, that's a desk.

1144
01:29:01,746 --> 01:29:03,805
I mean... wow.

1145
01:29:03,881 --> 01:29:09,648
<i>I, uh, I never really sat behind a desk before. I mean,
the one on the show is just a prop. This...</i>

1146
01:29:09,719 --> 01:29:13,621
- Where do you do your writing?
- Usually on the back of a napkin, sitting in a bar.

1147
01:29:16,026 --> 01:29:18,358
Well, there's a lot of history
to this desk.

1148
01:29:18,428 --> 01:29:22,455
The first time I sat behind it,
I had a sort of nervous chill.

1149
01:29:22,532 --> 01:29:26,400
Some of the greats and not-so-greats
have sat here.

1150
01:29:26,469 --> 01:29:28,232
Please.

1151
01:29:28,304 --> 01:29:30,272
Thank you.

1152
01:29:37,746 --> 01:29:39,873
Excuse me, Mr. President.

1153
01:29:39,948 --> 01:29:41,939
<i>- Hello?
- Tom? Tom?</i>

1154
01:29:42,017 --> 01:29:43,917
Eleanor? Hold on.

1155
01:29:43,986 --> 01:29:47,752
Mr. President, I'll just be a minute.
Thank you.

1156
01:29:47,823 --> 01:29:51,259
Tom, t-t-two guys broke into my hotel room.
I don't know what to do.

1157
01:29:51,326 --> 01:29:52,725
<i>Who? Who are they?</i>

1158
01:29:52,795 --> 01:29:56,162
They're connected with Delacroy.
I think they know I broke the code.

1159
01:29:56,231 --> 01:29:59,529
<i>- Code? What code?
- I figured out what caused the computer glitch.</i>

1160
01:29:59,600 --> 01:30:02,228
<i>- Where are you now?
- I'm in a shopping mall.</i>

1161
01:30:02,303 --> 01:30:04,794
<i>- Shopping?
- No, I'm not shopping.</i>

1162
01:30:04,872 --> 01:30:08,535
<i>- Why are you there?
- I didn't know what to do. I thought this was safer.</i>

1163
01:30:08,609 --> 01:30:11,737
Mr. President-elect, I'm on a bit of a tight schedule.

1164
01:30:12,313 --> 01:30:15,305
<i>- Listen, Eleanor, I'm with the President.
- What?</i>

1165
01:30:15,383 --> 01:30:17,943
I'm with the President of the US
in the Oval Office.

1166
01:30:18,019 --> 01:30:22,422
You're with the President?
You're in the Oval Office?

1167
01:30:22,957 --> 01:30:26,585
Look, Tom, I don't know what to do...
Hello?

1168
01:30:27,928 --> 01:30:29,657
Tom? Hello?

1169
01:30:29,730 --> 01:30:31,391
Hello?

1170
01:30:34,000 --> 01:30:35,968
Sorry, sir.

1171
01:30:42,342 --> 01:30:44,105
Wow.

1172
01:30:44,177 --> 01:30:46,941
It's been a pleasure, Mr. President. Thank you.

1173
01:30:47,013 --> 01:30:50,449
By the way, Mr. Dobbs,
I never thought you had a chance.

1174
01:30:50,517 --> 01:30:53,110
I underestimated you.

1175
01:30:53,185 --> 01:30:58,555
Well, just between you and me, Mr. President,
you didn't underestimate me at all.

1176
01:31:05,898 --> 01:31:07,593
Really? Why?

1177
01:31:08,134 --> 01:31:11,365
Oh, but that's so weird.
I never said anything to him.

1178
01:31:11,437 --> 01:31:14,998
No, he said stuff to me.
Like, what am I gonna say back?

1179
01:31:15,074 --> 01:31:17,634
But seri... Hold on a sec.

1180
01:31:17,710 --> 01:31:19,404
Hi. Sorry to interrupt.

1181
01:31:19,477 --> 01:31:23,208
I need a charger for this phone
that I can plug into my cigarette lighter.

1182
01:31:23,281 --> 01:31:26,978
We don't stock the charger for that anymore.
How long have you had that phone?

1183
01:31:27,051 --> 01:31:30,543
Well, it's not like it's a relic.
It's a year old.

1184
01:31:30,622 --> 01:31:32,954
Well, there is a problem -
it's a year old.

1185
01:31:39,998 --> 01:31:42,990
Mr. Stewart would like to see you at Delacroy.

1186
01:31:43,067 --> 01:31:45,933
- Why does he want to see me?
- He just wants to talk to you.

1187
01:31:46,003 --> 01:31:48,631
Reasonable people
can come to reasonable solutions.

1188
01:31:48,705 --> 01:31:51,469
You figured out the computer glitch.
You should be paid.

1189
01:31:51,542 --> 01:31:54,841
The Delacroy jet is at the private terminal.
I got her.

1190
01:32:05,622 --> 01:32:07,214
Get in.

1191
01:32:07,791 --> 01:32:09,383
Get in.

1192
01:32:22,972 --> 01:32:23,961
Shit!

1193
01:32:30,546 --> 01:32:31,877
Yeah.

1194
01:32:32,582 --> 01:32:35,380
I'm tracking her on her GPS.

1195
01:32:35,885 --> 01:32:37,580
Uh-huh.

1196
01:32:37,653 --> 01:32:42,214
Yes, first opportunity I get
I'll pick her up, bring her to the airport.

1197
01:32:42,290 --> 01:32:43,985
Uh-huh.

1198
01:32:46,561 --> 01:32:51,464
The FBI will confirm that you had no contact
with Eleanor Green prior to the election.

1199
01:32:51,533 --> 01:32:55,560
You're off the hook in terms of being involved
in any attempt to fix the election.

1200
01:32:55,637 --> 01:33:00,074
Sir, we've got to get you to the airport a little earlier.
A storm front is moving in.

1201
01:33:13,754 --> 01:33:15,984
Oh, for God's sake.

1202
01:33:38,611 --> 01:33:43,571
<i>Well, after Saturday Night Live tonight,
then I'm gonna be heading on.</i>

1203
01:33:43,650 --> 01:33:45,208
Why so soon?

1204
01:33:45,285 --> 01:33:49,244
Well, Menken thinks it's for the best.
No sense postponing the inevitable.

1205
01:33:49,322 --> 01:33:51,756
Will you be disappointed to go back to television?

1206
01:33:51,824 --> 01:33:55,225
Oh, no. I have a glorious
love-hate relationship with TV.

1207
01:33:55,295 --> 01:33:58,890
- How so?
- TV scares me. It makes everything seem credible.

1208
01:33:58,965 --> 01:34:00,431
Why is that so bad?

1209
01:34:00,499 --> 01:34:03,332
If everything seems credible,
nothing seems credible.

1210
01:34:04,036 --> 01:34:07,563
TV puts everybody in those boxes side by side.

1211
01:34:07,639 --> 01:34:12,406
On one side there's this certifiable lunatic
who says the Holocaust never happened.

1212
01:34:12,477 --> 01:34:18,211
Next to him is this noted, honored historian
who knows all about the Holocaust.

1213
01:34:18,283 --> 01:34:22,777
And now there they sit, side by side.
They look like equals.

1214
01:34:22,854 --> 01:34:28,485
<i>Everything they say seems credible. And so,
as it goes on, nothing seems credible anymore.</i>

1215
01:34:28,559 --> 01:34:30,322
We just stop listening.

1216
01:34:30,394 --> 01:34:33,955
<i>In the Times, 60% of the voters
would've voted for Dobbs if they could.</i>

1217
01:34:34,031 --> 01:34:38,593
Well, yeah. He sounds different.
That's why they can hear him.

1218
01:35:05,762 --> 01:35:06,751
Hello?

1219
01:35:06,830 --> 01:35:10,994
- My cellphone died and some guy is after me.
- I thought two guys were after you.

1220
01:35:11,067 --> 01:35:13,695
<i>- No, this is someone else.
- Who?</i>

1221
01:35:13,770 --> 01:35:16,739
I assume he's from Delacroy.
He has a pickup truck.

1222
01:35:17,307 --> 01:35:19,604
Eleanor, I... I think you need help.

1223
01:35:19,675 --> 01:35:21,939
He tried to abduct me from the mall!

1224
01:35:22,011 --> 01:35:24,445
In the mall. OK.

1225
01:35:24,513 --> 01:35:27,710
I think it has to do with the fact
that I figured everything out.

1226
01:35:30,185 --> 01:35:33,018
She's in a phone booth off Route 173.

1227
01:35:33,088 --> 01:35:36,455
You see, Mills and Kellogg both have double L's,

1228
01:35:36,525 --> 01:35:40,655
but Kellogg trumps him with double G's
and you trump him with double B's.

1229
01:35:40,729 --> 01:35:44,495
I don't know what that means, Eleanor.
Listen, where are you?

1230
01:35:44,566 --> 01:35:48,592
I don't know. I don't know where I am.
It's dark, there's a factory,

1231
01:35:48,669 --> 01:35:50,694
<i>I see a Christmas tree...</i>

1232
01:35:50,772 --> 01:35:52,535
I don't know where I am.

1233
01:35:52,607 --> 01:35:56,907
<i>- What do you want me to do now, sir?
- I'm willing to offer her big money. Big money.</i>

1234
01:35:56,978 --> 01:36:01,074
<i>She's running away now?
Why is she running away?</i>

1235
01:36:01,149 --> 01:36:04,710
<i>She's impossible. I don't know who she's talking to,
what she's saying.</i>

1236
01:36:04,786 --> 01:36:09,951
All right, go to the airport.
You go to BWI private terminal.

1237
01:36:10,024 --> 01:36:15,552
There's a plane there. We'll get on that plane, I'll take
you to New York and we'll solve your problem. OK?

1238
01:36:15,629 --> 01:36:19,656
Private terminal at the airport?
I don't know how to get to the airport.

1239
01:36:19,733 --> 01:36:24,033
All right, I'll try.
I'll look in my GPS or something.

1240
01:36:28,008 --> 01:36:30,738
Hello? Eleanor?

1241
01:36:35,015 --> 01:36:38,451
<i>More on that breaking news.
There has been a very serious traffic accident.</i>

1242
01:36:38,518 --> 01:36:43,420
<i>It is tying up traffic out on the Baltimore-Washington
Parkway just where it meets Route 495,</i>

1243
01:36:43,489 --> 01:36:45,252
<i>and that is the Capital Beltway.</i>

1244
01:36:45,324 --> 01:36:53,163
<i>There has been one serious injury. Police have
identified the injured woman as an Eleanor Green.</i>

1245
01:36:53,232 --> 01:36:54,460
Oh, my God.

1246
01:36:54,533 --> 01:36:57,969
<i>- If that sounds familiar, it's the same Eleanor Green...
- Menken!</i>

1247
01:36:58,037 --> 01:37:00,232
You have to see this!

1248
01:37:02,675 --> 01:37:05,940
Sir, we just got a report of an accident.
It's Eleanor Green.

1249
01:37:23,495 --> 01:37:25,190
Not now, please.

1250
01:37:25,263 --> 01:37:26,594
Excuse me.

1251
01:37:28,366 --> 01:37:30,834
Are you with the ambulance?
Eleanor Green?

1252
01:37:30,902 --> 01:37:33,995
- She's in a stable condition, sir.
- Thank you.

1253
01:37:38,308 --> 01:37:42,711
Oh, shit. Why does he have
to get himself into this mess?

1254
01:37:55,058 --> 01:38:01,257
Kid driving the truck is from Pittsburgh. Apparently
he lost control on the ice, went right off the road.

1255
01:38:06,969 --> 01:38:10,700
<i>- Tom, we've gotta get to Saturday Night Live.
- There's time.</i>

1256
01:38:21,784 --> 01:38:25,948
<i>Double B... double L... double G.</i>

1257
01:38:26,022 --> 01:38:30,185
Double B, double L, double G.

1258
01:38:30,258 --> 01:38:31,816
Double B...

1259
01:38:32,961 --> 01:38:35,759
double L... double G.

1260
01:38:39,968 --> 01:38:43,597
Double L, double G...

1261
01:38:51,446 --> 01:38:56,007
<i>They're trying to discredit her.
She's not psychotic, OK?</i>

1262
01:38:56,083 --> 01:38:58,745
I believe her, for Christ's sake. Look what they did.

1263
01:38:58,819 --> 01:39:02,983
<i>Last night you were willing to give it all up.
Now you want to do it again.</i>

1264
01:39:03,057 --> 01:39:05,218
Police said a truck lost control.

1265
01:39:05,292 --> 01:39:08,420
- She was trying to tell me something.
- It was snowing.

